import json
import csv
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
data = []
headers = []
dicts = []
jsonlines = []
finaldata = []
businessIDs = []
for line in open('yelp_academic_dataset_business.json', 'r', encoding='utf8'):
    jsonline = json.loads(line)
    if jsonline.get('city') == 'Philadelphia':
        jsonlines.append(jsonline)
        for i in jsonline.keys():
            if type(jsonline.get(i)) == dict:
                keys = jsonline.get(i).keys()
                values = jsonline.get(i).values()
                for z in keys:
                    if z not in headers:
                        headers.append(z)
                for y in values:
                    if "{" in y:
                        y = y[1:len(y) - 1]
                        splittedarr = y.split(',')
                        if splittedarr != ['']:
                            for x in splittedarr:
                                if x[0] == ' ':
                                    x = x[1:]
                                    newarr = []
                                    newarr = x.split(": ")
                                    if newarr[0] not in headers:
                                        headers.append(newarr[0])
            elif i not in headers:
                headers.append(i)

for line in jsonlines:
    mydata = []
    for x in range(len(headers)):
        mydata.append(np.nan)
    flag = True
    if line.get('city') == 'Philadelphia':

        for i in line.keys():
            if type(line.get(i)) == dict:
                keys = list(line.get(i).keys())
                values = list(line.get(i).values())
                countt = 0
                for y in values:
                    if "{" in y:
                        y = y[1:len(y)-1]
                        splittedarr = y.split(',')
                        if splittedarr != ['']:
                            for x in splittedarr:
                                if x[0] == ' ':
                                    x = x[1:]
                                newarr = []
                                newarr = x.split(": ")
                                if newarr[0] not in headers:
                                    headers.append(newarr[0])
                                    mydata.append(0)
                                mydata[headers.index(newarr[0])] = newarr[1]
                    else:
                        if keys[countt] not in headers:
                            headers.append(keys[countt])
                            mydata.append(countt)
                        mydata[headers.index(keys[countt])] = values[countt]
                    countt = countt + 1
                if None in values:
                    flag = False
            else:
                mydata[headers.index(i)] = line.get(i)
            if line.get(i) is None:
                flag = False
        if flag:
            businessIDs.append(mydata[0])
            data.append(mydata)

print(len(data))

maxlength = len(data[len(data)-1])
for i in data:
    if len(i) != maxlength:
        for x in range(maxlength-len(i)):
            i.append(np.nan)
with open('businesses.csv', 'w', newline='', encoding="utf8") as file:
    writer = csv.writer(file)
    writer.writerow(headers)
    writer.writerows(data)

reviewsheaders = []
reviewsdata = []

for line in open('yelp_academic_dataset_review.json', 'r', encoding='utf8'):
    jsonline = json.loads(line)
    if not reviewsheaders:
        reviewsheaders = jsonline.keys()
    if jsonline.get('business_id') in businessIDs:
        values = list(jsonline.values())
        values[7] = values[7].replace('\n', ' ')
        reviewsdata.append(values)

with open('reviews.csv', 'w', newline='', encoding="utf8") as file:
    writer = csv.writer(file)
    writer.writerow(reviewsheaders)
    writer.writerows(reviewsdata)

import pandas as pd
from datetime import timedelta
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import scipy
import seaborn as sns

visualDf = pd.DataFrame(columns=['Month', 'Star Rating', 'Counter'])
finalDf = pd.DataFrame(columns=['Month', 'Star Rating', 'Counter'])
finalcounter = 0
df = pd.read_csv('reviews.csv', low_memory=False)
df = df.sort_values(by=['business_id'])
df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date']).dt.date
counterrrr = 0
for i in df.business_id.unique():
    counterrrr +=1
    rating = 0
    month = 0
    uniqueBusinessDf = df[df['business_id'] == i]
    uniqueBusinessDf = uniqueBusinessDf.sort_values(by=['date'])
    counter = len(uniqueBusinessDf.index)
    minDate = uniqueBusinessDf['date'].min()
    newDateComparison = minDate + timedelta(days=30)
    lastComparison = minDate
    while counter > 0:
        uniqueToVisualDf = uniqueBusinessDf[(lastComparison <= uniqueBusinessDf['date']) & (uniqueBusinessDf['date'] < newDateComparison)]
        if len(uniqueToVisualDf.index) > 0:
            finalcounter = finalcounter + len(uniqueToVisualDf.index)
            counter = counter - len(uniqueToVisualDf.index)
            rating = uniqueToVisualDf['stars'].mean()
            row = {'Month': int(month), 'Star Rating': rating, 'Counter': len(uniqueToVisualDf.index)}
            appendDf = pd.DataFrame([row])
            visualDf = pd.concat([visualDf, appendDf], axis=0, ignore_index=True)
            rating = 0
        lastComparison = newDateComparison
        newDateComparison = newDateComparison + timedelta(days=30)
        month = month + 1
    del uniqueBusinessDf

fiveYearsVisualDf = visualDf[visualDf['Month'] <= 60]

sns.set_theme(style='darkgrid')

print("Mean star rating - all months - length: " + str(len(visualDf)))
sns.lineplot(x='Month', y='Star Rating', data=visualDf, ci=95)
plt.show()

print("Mean star rating - 5 years - length: " + str(len(fiveYearsVisualDf)))
sns.lineplot(x='Month', y='Star Rating', data=fiveYearsVisualDf, ci=95)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
from datetime import timedelta
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import scipy
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import pearsonr


df = pd.read_csv('RedfinPhila.tsv', sep='\t')
businessDf = pd.read_csv('businesses.csv', low_memory=False)
visualisationDf = pd.DataFrame(columns=['zip_code', 'city_value', 'number_of_businesses', 'average_stars_per_business'])
df[['region', 'postalcode']] = df['region'].str.split('Code: ', expand=True)
tsvDf = df[['postalcode', 'median_sale_price']]
# print(tsvDf)
for i in tsvDf.postalcode.unique():
    price = tsvDf[tsvDf['postalcode'] == i]['median_sale_price'].mean()
    starsAvg = businessDf[businessDf['postal_code'] == int(i)]['stars'].mean()
    numOfBusinesses = len(businessDf[businessDf['postal_code'] == int(i)])
    row = {'zip_code': i, 'city_value': float(price), 'number_of_businesses': float(numOfBusinesses),
           'average_stars_per_business': float(starsAvg)}
    appendDf = pd.DataFrame([row])
    visualisationDf = pd.concat([visualisationDf, appendDf], axis=0, ignore_index=True)

visualDf = visualisationDf[visualisationDf['number_of_businesses'] > 0]
sns.pairplot(visualDf)
pearsonTable = visualDf.corr(method='pearson')
print("Pearson correlation coefficients table: ")
print(pearsonTable)
for i in ['city_value', 'number_of_businesses', 'average_stars_per_business']:
    for y in ['city_value', 'number_of_businesses', 'average_stars_per_business']:
        prsn, p = pearsonr(visualDf[i], visualDf[y])
        pearsonTable[i][y] = p
print("P-Values table: ")
print(pearsonTable)

plt.show()

# AFTER FOR 200K>>>>>
over200kDf = visualisationDf[visualisationDf['city_value'] > 200000]
over200df = over200kDf[over200kDf['number_of_businesses'] > 0]
sns.pairplot(over200df)
pearsonTableOver200k = over200df.corr(method='pearson')
print("Pearson correlation coefficients table for over 200k: ")
print(pearsonTableOver200k)
for i in ['city_value', 'number_of_businesses', 'average_stars_per_business']:
    for y in ['city_value', 'number_of_businesses', 'average_stars_per_business']:
        prsn, p = pearsonr(over200df[i], over200df[y])
        pearsonTableOver200k[i][y] = p
print("P-Values table for over 200k: ")
print(pearsonTableOver200k)

plt.show()

print("All Regions Dataframe length: " + str(len(visualDf)))
print("Expensive Regions Dataframe length: " + str(len(over200df)))

import pandas as pd
from datetime import timedelta
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import scipy
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import ttest_ind

businessDf = pd.read_csv('businesses.csv', low_memory=False)
restaurantsToViewDf = pd.DataFrame(columns=['price_range', 'star_rating'])
attireToViewDf = pd.DataFrame(columns=['dresscode', 'star_rating'])

cheapRestaurantsDf = businessDf[(businessDf['RestaurantsPriceRange2'] == '1') |
                                (businessDf['RestaurantsPriceRange2'] == '2')]
expRestaurantsDf = businessDf[(businessDf['RestaurantsPriceRange2'] == '3') |
                              (businessDf['RestaurantsPriceRange2'] == '4')]
formalAttireDf = businessDf[(businessDf['RestaurantsAttire'] == "'dressy'") |
                            (businessDf['RestaurantsAttire'] == "u'dressy'") |
                            (businessDf['RestaurantsAttire'] == "'formal'") |
                            (businessDf['RestaurantsAttire'] == "u'formal'")]
casualAttireDf = businessDf[(businessDf['RestaurantsAttire'] == "'casual'") |
                            (businessDf['RestaurantsAttire'] == "u'casual'")]

cheapstars = cheapRestaurantsDf['stars'].tolist()
expstars = expRestaurantsDf['stars'].tolist()
formalstars = formalAttireDf['stars'].tolist()
casualstars = casualAttireDf['stars'].tolist()

for i in range(len(cheapRestaurantsDf['RestaurantsPriceRange2'])):
    pricerange = 'cheap'
    row = {'price_range': pricerange, 'star_rating': cheapstars[i]}
    appendDf = pd.DataFrame([row])
    restaurantsToViewDf = pd.concat([restaurantsToViewDf, appendDf], axis=0, ignore_index=True)
for i in range(len(expRestaurantsDf['RestaurantsPriceRange2'])):
    pricerange = 'expensive'
    row = {'price_range': pricerange, 'star_rating': expstars[i]}
    appendDf = pd.DataFrame([row])
    restaurantsToViewDf = pd.concat([restaurantsToViewDf, appendDf], axis=0, ignore_index=True)

for i in range(len(formalAttireDf['RestaurantsAttire'])):
    dresscode = 'formal'
    row = {'dresscode': dresscode, 'star_rating': formalstars[i]}
    appendDf = pd.DataFrame([row])
    attireToViewDf = pd.concat([attireToViewDf, appendDf], axis=0, ignore_index=True)
for i in range(len(casualAttireDf['RestaurantsAttire'])):
    dresscode = 'casual'
    row = {'dresscode': dresscode, 'star_rating': casualstars[i]}
    appendDf = pd.DataFrame([row])
    attireToViewDf = pd.concat([attireToViewDf, appendDf], axis=0, ignore_index=True)

print("-Cheap vs Expensive- dataframe length: " + str(len(restaurantsToViewDf)))

ax = sns.pointplot(x="price_range",
                   y="star_rating",
                   data=restaurantsToViewDf,
                   errorbar=('ci', 95), join=False)
plt.show()
print("Cheap Values involved: " + str(len(restaurantsToViewDf["star_rating"][restaurantsToViewDf["price_range"] == 'cheap'])))
print("Expensive Values involved: " + str(len(restaurantsToViewDf["star_rating"][restaurantsToViewDf["price_range"] == 'expensive'])))
print("-Cheap vs Expensive- Ttest and P-value:")
print(ttest_ind(restaurantsToViewDf["star_rating"][restaurantsToViewDf["price_range"] == 'cheap'],
                restaurantsToViewDf["star_rating"][restaurantsToViewDf["price_range"] == 'expensive']))

ax = sns.pointplot(y="price_range",

plt.show()

print(expected)

import pandas as pd
from datetime import timedelta
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import scipy
import seaborn as sns

df = pd.read_csv('RedfinPhila.tsv', sep='\t')
businessDf = pd.read_csv('businesses.csv', low_memory=False)
df[['region', 'postalcode']] = df['region'].str.split('Code: ', expand=True)
tsvDf = df[['postalcode', 'median_sale_price']]
categoriesarray = ['cityvalue']
allcategoriesvaluescounter = []
counter = 0
for i in tsvDf.postalcode.unique():
    categoriesvaluescounter = len(categoriesarray)*[0]
    price = tsvDf[tsvDf['postalcode'] == i]['median_sale_price'].mean()
    categories = businessDf[businessDf['postal_code'] == int(i)]['categories']
    categoriesvaluescounter[0] = price
    if len(categories) != 0:
        for y in categories:
            categoriessplit = y.split(', ')
            for x in categoriessplit:
                if x not in categoriesarray:
                    categoriesarray.append(x)
                    categoriesvaluescounter.append(0)
                categoriesvaluescounter[categoriesarray.index(x)] += 1
        if 'Restaurants' in categoriesarray:
            del categoriesvaluescounter[categoriesarray.index('Restaurants')]
            categoriesarray.remove('Restaurants')
        for y in range(1, len(categoriesvaluescounter)):
            categoriesvaluescounter[y] = int(categoriesvaluescounter[y]) / (len(categories))
        counter += 1
        allcategoriesvaluescounter.append(categoriesvaluescounter)
visualisationDf = pd.DataFrame(columns=categoriesarray)
for i in allcategoriesvaluescounter:
    if len(i) != len(categoriesarray):
        for x in range(len(categoriesarray) - len(i)):
            i.append(0)
for i in range(len(allcategoriesvaluescounter)):
    row = {categoriesarray[x]: allcategoriesvaluescounter[i][x] for x in range(len(allcategoriesvaluescounter[i]))}
    appendDf = pd.DataFrame([row])
    visualisationDf = pd.concat([visualisationDf, appendDf], axis=0, ignore_index=True)
cityvalues = visualisationDf['cityvalue'].to_list()
cityvalues.sort()
print("City Values Sorted Array: ")
print(cityvalues)
print("Cities-Regions involved: " + str(len(cityvalues)))
del categoriesarray[0]
del categoriesarray[0]
closeDistance = []
farDistance = []

for i in range(0, len(cityvalues)-1):
    visualDf = visualisationDf[visualisationDf['cityvalue'] <= (cityvalues[i+1])].astype(float)
    visualDf = visualDf[(cityvalues[i]) <= visualDf['cityvalue']].astype(float)
    visualDf = visualDf.set_index("cityvalue")
    transposed = visualDf.T
    # print(transposed)
    columns = transposed.columns.to_list()
    # print(columns)
    distance = 0
    first = list(transposed[columns[0]])
    second = list(transposed[columns[1]])
    for x in range(0, len(first)):
        distance += abs(first[x] - second[x])
    closeDistance.append(distance)

for i in range(0, len(cityvalues)-20, 1):
    visualDf = visualisationDf[visualisationDf['cityvalue'] >= (cityvalues[i+20])].astype(float)
    visualDf2 = visualisationDf[visualisationDf['cityvalue'] == (cityvalues[i])].astype(float)
    visualDf = visualDf.set_index("cityvalue")
    visualDf2 = visualDf2.set_index("cityvalue")
    transposed = visualDf.T
    transposed2 = visualDf2.T
    columns = transposed.columns.to_list()
    columns2 = transposed2.columns.to_list()
    distance = 0
    first = list(transposed[columns[0]])
    second = list(transposed2[columns2[0]])
    for y in range(0, len(columns)):
        for x in range(0, len(first)):
            distance += abs(first[x] - second[x])
    farDistance.append(distance/len(columns))             # mean distance of a city and its dissimilar cities
    
print("Similar Price Regions Variational-Distance mean: " + str(sum(closeDistance)/len(closeDistance)))
print("Dissimilar Price Regions Variational-Distance mean: " + str(sum(farDistance)/len(farDistance)))
print("Every dataframe used has a row for every category which is involved in all zip codes.")
print("Dataframe rows length (UNIQUE CATEGORIES) : "+ str(len(transposed2)))
